The paper focuses on parsing delimiter-separated data formats, which is a common task in database systems (cs.DB). The proposed algorithm is massively parallel and targets GPUs, which are often used for high-performance computing and data processing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions stream processing and in-situ querying, which are related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and programming languages (cs.PL), respectively. Finally, the paper involves finite state machine (FSM) simulation, which is a topic in computer architecture (cs.AR).
